{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0ef10d7c-48f8-4956-b135-67dac02b0eee","content":"Here are the issues I found in the template.json:\n\n1. **Missing required field `identity`** — Every .NET template must have an `identity` field (a unique identifier for the template).\n\n2. **Invalid `datatype` value** — `\"invalid-type\"` on line 9 is not a valid datatype. Valid values are: `bool`, `choice`, `float`, `int`, `hex`, `text`, `string`.\n\n3. **Missing `$schema`** (recommended) — Adding the schema reference helps with editor validation:\n   ```json\n   \"$schema\": \"http://json.schemastore.org/template\"\n   ```\n\nThe most critical issues are **#1** (will cause template engine errors) and **#2** (the parameter won't work correctly).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"478a3f1a-c115-49bb-aa96-04bb3930f875","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Let me analyze this template.json file. This is a .NET template configuration file (used by `dotnet new`). Let me check for issues:\n\n1. **Missing required fields**: The `template.json` schema requires:\n   - `$schema` - recommended but not strictly required\n   - `author` ✓\n   - `classifications` ✓\n   - `identity` - **MISSING** - this is required\n   - `name` ✓\n   - `shortName` ✓\n   - `sourceName` - optional\n\n2. **Invalid datatype**: The `datatype` value `\"invalid-type\"` is not a valid datatype. \n\nValid options are `bool`, `choice`, `float`, `int`, `hex`, `text`, or `string`.\n\n3. **Missing `$schema`**: Not required but recommended for validation.\n\nSo I've found three main issues: a missing required `identity` field, an invalid datatype value, and the absence of a schema reference.","outputTokens":398,"requestId":"480F:BBE67:E8DED:1175D0:69EABD7A"},"id":"5d8b60d0-d5c9-4fa9-84c7-8cc7ce86c521","timestamp":"2026-04-24T00:47:00.068Z","parentId":"871f0d78-9805-4d19-a6af-8ebda4ae8214"}
